## Integration Tests

### Markers for Slow/External Tests

```python
# tests/integration/test_external_api.py

import pytest

@pytest.mark.integration
@pytest.mark.slow
def test_fetches_real_data_from_api():
    """Integration test with real external API."""
    client = ApiClient(base_url="https://api.example.com")
    data = client.fetch("items", limit=10)
    
    assert len(data) > 0
    assert "id" in data[0]
```

### Running Integration Tests

```bash
# Skip integration tests by default
pytest -m "not integration"

# Run only integration tests
pytest -m integration

# Run all tests
pytest
```

### pytest.ini Configuration

```ini
[pytest]
markers =
    integration: marks tests as integration tests (deselect with '-m "not integration"')
    slow: marks tests as slow (deselect with '-m "not slow"')
    smoke: critical path smoke tests (run with -m smoke)
```

